editorial:
**Brute force**: har closing bracket ke liye nearest opening dhundhna messy hai.

**Stack approach**: jab opening bracket aaye `(` `[` `{` toh stack mein push kar. Jab closing aaye toh top pop karke check kar ki matching opening hai ya nahi. End mein stack empty honi chahiye.

Non-bracket chars (letters, digits) ko skip karna hai — sirf brackets pe focus.

```js
function isBalanced(s){
  const m={')':'(',']':'[','}':'{'};
  const st=[];
  for(const c of s){
    if(c==='('||c==='['||c==='{') st.push(c);
    else if(c in m){
      if(st.pop()!==m[c]) return false;
    }
  }
  return st.length===0;
}
```

**Edge cases**: empty string return true, sirf openings ya sirf closings false. Stack ka top represent karta hai sabse recent unmatched opening — LIFO order matlab innermost pehle close hoga.

**Complexity**: O(n) time, O(n) space worst case (saare openings).

