editorial:
**Idea**: Do parallel stacks rakh — main stack `st` aur `ms` jismein har position ka 'minimum so far' store hai.

Push x: `st.push(x)`, `ms.push(min(top of ms, x))`.
Pop: dono se pop.
Top: `st` ka top.
Min: `ms` ka top.

Is design problem ko function-style mein ops array iterate karke implement karenge.

```js
function minStack(ops){
  const st=[], ms=[], out=[];
  for(const op of ops){
    if(op[0]==='push'){
      st.push(op[1]);
      ms.push(ms.length===0 ? op[1] : Math.min(ms[ms.length-1], op[1]));
      out.push(null);
    } else if(op[0]==='pop'){
      st.pop(); ms.pop(); out.push(null);
    } else if(op[0]==='top'){
      out.push(st[st.length-1]);
    } else { // 'min'
      out.push(ms[ms.length-1]);
    }
  }
  return out;
}
```

**Complexity**: O(1) per op, O(n) total space.

