editorial:
**Trick**: Two stacks `inSt` (push side) aur `outSt` (pop/peek side). Enqueue hamesha `inSt` mein push kar. Dequeue/peek ke liye agar `outSt` empty hai toh `inSt` se saare pop karke `outSt` mein push kar — order reverse ho jata hai aur head accessible.

```js
function twoStackQueue(ops){
  const inSt=[], outSt=[], out=[];
  for(const op of ops){
    if(op[0]==='enqueue'){ inSt.push(op[1]); out.push(null); }
    else if(op[0]==='dequeue'){
      if(outSt.length===0) while(inSt.length) outSt.push(inSt.pop());
      out.push(outSt.length ? outSt.pop() : null);
    } else { // peek
      if(outSt.length===0) while(inSt.length) outSt.push(inSt.pop());
      out.push(outSt.length ? outSt[outSt.length-1] : null);
    }
  }
  return out;
}
```

**Amortized analysis**: har element max ek baar `inSt`->`outSt` move hota hai, so amortized O(1).

**Complexity**: O(n) total, O(n) space.

